Nigeria star Taiwo Awoniyi scored a brace as Union Berlin claimed a 3-2 win over Bochum in their last Bundesliga game on Saturday. After Grischa Promel scored the opening goal of the match in the fifth minute in favour of Berlin, Awoniyi added the second in the 25th minute. Bochum scored their second in the 55th minute through Simon Zoller before equalizing in the 79th minute through Eduard Lowen. Awoniyi scored the vital goal in the 88th minute to make sure Berlin – with 57 points and fifth on the log – ended the season on a winning note.   Erling Haaland scores in emotional Dortmund farewell     Wydad qualify for CAF Champions League final     YSFON backs Gawuna for Kano governorship seat   Meanwhile, Christopher Nkunku’s RB Leipzig managed to hold onto fourth place despite a 1-1 draw against Arminia Bielefeld. Nkunku, a Democratic Republic of Congo prospect, was part of the starting eleven but did not manage to score despite playing in the entire period of the league duel. Janni-Luca Serra with an assist from Robin Hack, scored for Bielefeld in the 70th minute, before Nkunku’s side fought back and pegged the score to a 1-1 draw following Vilmos Orban’s goal in the third minute of added time. Leipzig have ended the season with 58 points, 19 fewer than Bayern Munich, the Bundesliga champions, and six fewer than Bayer Leverkusen, who are third.